  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The hypothesis is that radiofrequency ablation combined or not with resection may allow a&#xD;
      local control (the liver) in patients suffering from unresectable colorectal liver&#xD;
      metastases. Patients may have benefit or not from a preoperative (neoadjuvant) chemotherapy.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
